---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services"
  description="Londonberry offers AI-powered rapid prototyping, AI strategy consulting, and strategic product management for startups, sports tech companies, and growing businesses."
>
  <!-- Rapid Prototyping -->
  <section id="rapid-prototyping" class="py-20 md:py-24 border-b border-muted/30">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <img src="/images/service_development.png" alt="" class="w-14 h-14 mb-5" />
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-heading">Rapid Prototyping</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-3">
          <p class="text-lg text-body/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Speed wins. We build working prototypes in days using AI-assisted development — not wireframes that sit in a slide deck for months. You get real software you can click through, test with users, and show to investors.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-body/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Our approach pairs experienced product development with the latest AI coding tools to compress timelines without cutting corners. The result: you validate ideas faster, waste less money on wrong directions, and get to market ahead of the competition.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-heading/60 mb-4">What This Looks Like</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-body/80">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Idea-to-clickable-prototype in 1-2 weeks</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>AI-assisted full-stack development (web & mobile)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Iterative builds — ship, learn, improve, repeat</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Production-grade code from day one, not throwaway demos</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI Strategy -->
  <section id="ai-strategy" class="py-20 md:py-24 border-b border-muted/30">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <img src="/images/service_management.png" alt="" class="w-14 h-14 mb-5" />
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-heading">AI Strategy & Consulting</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-3">
          <p class="text-lg text-body/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Every company is being told they need AI. Few know where to start. We cut through the hype and help you identify where AI can genuinely move the needle in your business — and where it's just noise.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-body/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Whether you're looking to automate internal workflows, add intelligence to your product, or figure out how AI agents can work alongside your team, we bring hands-on experience building with these tools every day.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-heading/60 mb-4">What This Looks Like</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-body/80">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>AI readiness assessments and opportunity mapping</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Tool selection and integration strategy</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>AI agent design and workflow automation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Team training on AI-assisted development practices</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Product Management -->
  <section id="product-management" class="py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <img src="/images/service_ui.png" alt="" class="w-14 h-14 mb-5" />
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-heading">Product Management</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-3">
          <p class="text-lg text-body/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Great software starts with great product thinking. We bring strategic product management to companies that need experienced guidance on what to build, why, and in what order.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-body/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            This isn't project management — tracking tickets and running standups. This is the hard work of understanding your market, defining your product vision, and making the tradeoff decisions that separate products people love from ones they tolerate.
          </p>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-heading/60 mb-4">What This Looks Like</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-body/80">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Product vision, strategy, and roadmap development</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Feature prioritization and scope definition</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>User research and market validation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-primary font-bold mt-0.5">&#10003;</span>
              <span>Fractional CPO/VP Product for startups and growing teams</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-heading text-white py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Not sure what you need?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Most projects touch all three. Drop us a line and we'll figure out the right approach together.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-white text-heading px-8 py-3 rounded-md font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wide hover:bg-white/90 transition-colors inline-block">
        Start a Conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
